<font size=24>可是我爱你</font>
But I love you?

151
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:26,160
<font size=24>便大的我吃什么?</font>
Tihs-ym-tae. WO What?

152
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:28,950
<font size=24>便..大..</font>
Tihs-ym-tae.

153
00:19:31,870 --> 00:19:33,540
<font size=24>的..我..吃..</font>
-Eat. -Eat.

154
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:36,750
<font size=24>吃我的大便</font>
-Ym, my. -My.

155
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:38,750
<font size=24>你这只肮脏的猪</font>
Tihs. Eat my shit.

156
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:41,510
<font size=24>你这个肮脏...</font>
You filthy fiend!

157
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:44,590
<font size=24>-你这个肮脏!  -嘘...</font>
-You filthy! -Shh....

158
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:51,230
<font size=24>我的音乐</font>
My music.

159
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:54,900
<font size=24>他们没有我就开始了</font>
They've started without me.

160
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:11,560
<font size=24>那就是莫扎特</font>
That was Mozart!

161
00:21:12,850 --> 00:21:17,980
<font size=24>当我面前打滚嘻戏的小丑</font>
That giggling, dirty creature I'd just seen crawling on the floor.

162
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:22,480
<font size=24>我觉得演奏会进行得很顺利没错</font>
-I think that went well, don't you? -Indeed.

163
00:21:22,690 --> 00:21:26,200
<font size=24>维也纳人就是会欣赏优美的音乐</font>
The Viennese know good music, don't you think?

164
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:27,450
<font size=24>当然</font>
Certainly.

165
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:32,200
<font size=24>尊敬的陛下</font>
Your Grace.

166
00:21:33,540 --> 00:21:36,620
<font size=24>莫扎特</font>
Ah, Mozart.

167
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,710
<font size=24>-为什么?  -什么为什么  陛下?</font>
-Why? -Why what, sir?

168
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:44,880
<font size=24>为什么我要在我的宾客面前</font>
Why do I have to be humiliated in front of my guests...

169
00:21:45,090 --> 00:21:47,380
<font size=24>受仆人的羞辱?</font>
by one of my own servants?

170
00:21:47,630 --> 00:21:51,180
<font size=24>你真是太得寸进尺了</font>
The more license I allow you, the more you take.

171
00:21:51,390 --> 00:21:55,310
<font size=24>如果陛下不喜欢我 你可以请我离开</font>
If His Grace is not satisfied, he can dismiss me.

172
00:21:55,980 --> 00:21:59,560
<font size=24>我希望你能立刻回沙德堡</font>
I wish you to return immediately to Salzburg.

173
00:21:59,730 --> 00:22:03,690
<font size=24>-你父亲在那里耐心的等你  -不  陛下!</font>
-Your father is waiting for you there Patiently. -No, Your Grace!

174
00:22:04,230 --> 00:22:09,240
<font size=24>我将更喜欢您解雇我  很明显的我未能使你满意</font>
I would prefer you dismissed me. It's obvious I don't satisfy.

175
00:22:09,410 --> 00:22:14,830
<font size=24>我并不打算请你离开  你还是要当我的仆人</font>
I have no intention of dismissing you. You will remain in my service...

176
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,710
<font size=24>同时学点规矩</font>
and learn your place.

177
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:57,950
<font size=24>在乐谱上看来一点也不起眼</font>
On the page it looked....Nothing!

178
00:22:58,210 --> 00:23:02,250
<font size=24>非常简单的前奏  几乎有点可笑</font>
The beginning simple, almost comic.

179
00:23:03,460 --> 00:23:08,920
<font size=24>只有一个节拍  低音管  低音号</font>
Just a pulse.Bassoons, basset horns...

180
00:23:09,130 --> 00:23:12,130
<font size=24>好像生锈的铁盒子一样</font>
like a rusty squeezebox.

181
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:17,640
<font size=24>然后  突然间</font>
And then, suddenly...

182
00:23:17,810 --> 00:23:20,060
<font size=24>出现高音的双簧管</font>
high above it...

183
00:23:21,770 --> 00:23:24,060
<font size=24>一根双簧管</font>
an oboe.

184
00:23:26,190 --> 00:23:29,490
<font size=24>一个音符不变地飘浮着</font>
A single note, hanging there, unwavering.

185
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:36,700
<font size=24>直到黑管接手</font>
Until...a clarinet took it over...

186
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:43,500
<font size=24>甜美的调子  充满了欢欣</font>
sweetened it into a phrase of such delight.

187
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:51,800
<font size=24>这可不是马戏团猴子所能作的乐曲</font>
This was no composition by a performing monkey.

188
00:23:54,220 --> 00:23:57,970
<font size=24>是我未曾听过的音乐</font>
This was a music I had never heard.

189
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:04,730
<font size=24>充满了无法满足的情感</font>
Filled with such longing, such unfulfillable longing.

190
00:24:06,770 --> 00:24:10,150
<font size=24>就如同听到上帝的声音一般</font>
It seemed to me I was hearing the voice of God.

191
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:11,610
<font size=24>对不起!</font>
Excuse me.

192
00:24:13,110 --> 00:24:14,860
<font size=24>为什么?</font>
But why?

193
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:20,660
<font size=24>为什么上帝却选了一个年幼无知的小孩作为他声音的工具呢?</font>
Why would God choose an obscene child to be his instrument?

194
00:24:21,120 --> 00:24:23,370
<font size=24>我绝对不相信</font>
It was not to be believed.

195
00:24:23,540 --> 00:24:28,210
<font size=24>这个地方曾经有过意外  一定是</font>
This piece had to be an accident. It had to be.

196
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:34,010
<font size=24>好多了</font>
It better be.

197
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:37,470
<font size=24>这个莫扎特有多好?</font>
How good is he, this Mozart?

198
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:43,270
<font size=24>他真是完美极了  陛下  我上个月听过他相当杰出的歌剧</font>
He's remarkable, Majesty. I heard an extraordinary opera of his last month.

199
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:46,900
<font size=24>-《克里特王》那出歌剧-那真的是最平凡的作品</font>
-Idomeneo, King of Crete.  That?

200
00:24:47,690 --> 00:24:50,230
<font size=24>一个无聊的作品 我也听过</font>
A tiresome piece. I heard it too.

201
00:24:50,900 --> 00:24:52,150
<font size=24>无聊?</font>
Tiresome?

202
00:24:53,070 --> 00:24:57,360
<font size=24>一个年轻人不自量力</font>
A young man trying to impress beyond his abilities.

203
00:24:57,570 --> 00:25:02,290
<font size=24>太多加料  太多音符</font>
Too much spice. Too many notes.

204
00:25:02,910 --> 00:25:07,920
<font size=24>陛下  那是我近年听到最好作品</font>
Majesty...it was the most promising work I've heard in years.

205
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:11,750
<font size=24>那我们应努力将他争取过来</font>
Then, we should make some effort to acquire him.

206
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:16,300
<font size=24>维也纳可以用个好德国作曲家吧</font>
We could use a good German composer in Vienna, surely?

207
00:25:16,550 --> 00:25:21,180
<font size=24>只要价码合理  我相信他会有兴趣的</font>
I'm sure he could be tempted with the right offer. Say...

208
00:25:22,020 --> 00:25:25,430
<font size=24>-为了我们的国家歌剧院  做一曲德文的歌剧</font>
an opera in German for our National Theater.

209
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:26,850
<font size=24>太好了  陛下</font>
Excellent, sire!

210
00:25:27,810 --> 00:25:30,860
<font size=24>但陛下  不要德文好不好</font>
But not German. I beg, Your Majesty.

211
00:25:31,070 --> 00:25:35,440
<font size=24>意大利文才是得体的歌剧语言</font>
Italian is the proper language for opera.

212
00:25:35,610 --> 00:25:38,360
<font size=24>受过教育的人都会同意这一点</font>
All educated people agree on that.

213
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:44,910
<font size=24>你认为如何?  内廷大臣?</font>
Mm-hm. What do you think, chamberlain?

214
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:49,790
<font size=24>我认为是该有本国语言歌剧的时候了</font>
In my opinion, it's time we had a piece in our own language.

215
00:25:50,380 --> 00:25:54,460
<font size=24>让老百姓听德文吧!</font>
Plain German for plain people.

216
00:25:57,470 --> 00:25:59,970
<font size=24>卡普麦斯特(宫庭乐团团长)你呢?</font>
Kapellmeister?

217
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:05,270
<font size=24>我同意剧场监督的看法</font>
Majesty...I must agree with Herr Direttore.

218
00:26:06,810 --> 00:26:15,900
<font size=24>德文...太粗野了  不适合歌剧</font>
German is...scusate...too brute for singing.

219
00:26:19,570 --> 00:26:24,660
<font size=24>宫庭作曲家  你认为呢?</font>
Court composer...what do you think?

220
00:26:25,660 --> 00:26:29,790
<font size=24>我认为将莫扎特请来维也纳是很有趣的构想</font>
I think it's an interesting notion to keep Mozart in Vienna.

221
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:36,010
<font size=24>这会使得大主教非常的愤怒也许这是陛下的企图</font>
It should infuriate the archbishop...if that is Your Majesty's intention.

222
00:26:36,170 --> 00:26:39,680
<font size=24>你说对了  宫庭作曲家</font>
You are cattivo, court composer.

223
00:26:41,970 --> 00:26:46,930
<font size=24>我要见见这年轻人  安排一愉快的欢迎仪式给他</font>
I want to meet this young man. Arrange a pleasant welcome for him.

224
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:50,190
<font size=24>好了  就这么办</font>
Well, there it is!

225
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:16,210
<font size=24>感谢你  上帝</font>
Grazie, signore.

226
00:27:23,220 --> 00:27:30,230
<font size=24>这顶假发太适合你了  看起来实在太棒了</font>
This is a beautiful wig for you. It looks so marvelous and I love it.

227
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:31,690
<font size=24>另一顶</font>
The other one.

228
00:27:33,730 --> 00:27:37,190
<font size=24>我想你会喜欢这一顶</font>
Here is the other one. I think you will love it.

229
00:27:44,410 --> 00:27:48,080
<font size=24>-你喜欢吗?  -他们都太美了</font>
-How do you like it? -They're all so beautiful!

230
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:51,040
<font size=24>我三顶全要我为什么没有三个头?</font>
Why don't I have three heads?

231
00:27:52,330 --> 00:27:55,960
<font size=24>那很有趣 三个头</font>
This is funny! Three heads!

232
00:27:58,710 --> 00:28:01,670
<font size=24>-早安陛下  -早安</font>
Good morning.  Morning, Your Majesty.

233
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:07,220
<font size=24>今天为我准备了什么?</font>
What do you have for me today?

234
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:11,560
<font size=24>陛下  莫扎特先生  他怎么样</font>
-Your Majesty, Herr Mozart.  Yes, what about him?

235
00:28:11,770 --> 00:28:13,730
<font size=24>-他已经来了</font>
He's here.

236
00:28:16,060 --> 00:28:17,940
<font size=24>-就这样子了  很好</font>
Well, there it is. Good!

237
00:28:18,110 --> 00:28:23,610
<font size=24>陛下  我希望你不会认为不妥  我写了一个短曲欢迎他</font>
I hope you won't find it improper, but I've written a march in his honor.

238
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:27,910
<font size=24>想得真周到  我能看看吗?</font>
What a charming idea, court composer. May I see?

239
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:32,370
<font size=24>只是个小曲罢了</font>
Just a....Just a trifle, of course.

240
00:28:34,710 --> 00:28:35,960
<font size=24>我能试试吗?</font>
May I try it?

241
00:28:36,790 --> 00:28:38,290
<font size=24>我的荣幸</font>
Majesty!

242
00:28:40,130 --> 00:28:42,510
<font size=24>我们来开心一下</font>
Let's have some fun.

243
00:28:57,020 --> 00:29:00,150
<font size=24>太棒了  宫庭作曲家!</font>
Delightful, court composer!

244
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:04,110
<font size=24>他进来时我能演奏吗?</font>
May I play it when he comes in?

245
00:29:05,070 --> 00:29:10,660
<font size=24>-悉听尊便  先生!  -带莫扎特来  但..慢慢的</font>
-You do me too much honor. -Bring in Herr Mozart. But slowly.

246
00:29:10,910 --> 00:29:13,540
<font size=24>我要给他惊喜</font>
I need a minute to practice.

247
00:29:37,020 --> 00:29:38,350
<font size=24>很好  先生!  继续</font>
Good, continue.

248
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:43,070
<font size=24>很好  继续</font>
G, Majesty.

249
00:29:46,030 --> 00:29:48,110
<font size=24>太完美了</font>
Excellent!

250
00:29:56,790 --> 00:29:59,540
<font size=24>-非常棒  陛下</font>
Very good, Majesty.

251
00:30:01,590 --> 00:30:04,300
<font size=24>快! 向上</font>
Tempo! Up.

252
00:30:04,510 --> 00:30:10,050
<font size=24>轻轻然后强烈!  它他是进行曲  陛下  重复</font>
Lightly, then strongly! It's a march, Majesty. Again.

253
00:30:49,090 --> 00:30:51,090
<font size=24>喝彩声  陛下!</font>
Bravo, Majesty!

254
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:57,020
<font size=24>先生们  请不要如此热情  谢谢</font>
Gentlemen, please. A little less enthusiasm, I beg you.

255
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:01,770
<font size=24>-莫扎特-陛下</font>
-Mozart. -Majesty.

256
00:31:02,020 --> 00:31:05,730
<font size=24>不  我可不是教宗</font>
No, please. It's not a holy relic.

257
00:31:08,610 --> 00:31:12,450
<font size=24>我们以前曾经见过面...就在这个大房间里面</font>
You know, we have met before. In this very room.

258
00:31:12,660 --> 00:31:17,580
<font size=24>也许你不记得  你当时只有六岁  就已经演奏了最棒的协奏曲</font>
You don't recall. You were only 6. He was giving a delightful concert!

259
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:20,870
<font size=24>他从椅子爬下来时还滑了一跤</font>
As he got off the stool, he fell.

260
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:24,960
<font size=24>我的妹妹安东尼扶他起来  你们知他怎么了?</font>
My sister Antoinette helped him up. Know what he did?

261
00:31:25,170 --> 00:31:30,090
<font size=24>他抱住她  然后说：你愿意嫁给我吗?</font>
He jumped into her arms and said, "Will you marry me? Yes or no?"

262
00:31:33,970 --> 00:31:37,810
<font size=24>你一定认识各位先生吧!  范史威登公爵</font>
You know all these gentlemen. The Baron Van Swieten.

263
00:31:37,970 --> 00:31:41,770
<font size=24>-年轻人  我相当喜欢你的作品  -谢谢</font>
-I'm a great admirer of yours. -Thank you.

264
00:31:41,980 --> 00:31:45,440
<font size=24>卡普麦斯特先生</font>
Kapellmeister Bonno. Signore.

265
00:31:45,650 --> 00:31:46,900
<font size=24>我的荣幸</font>
My pleasure.

266
00:31:47,110 --> 00:31:50,740
<font size=24>我们的歌剧院长  罗森保伯爵</font>
The Director of Opera, Count Orsini-Rosenberg.

267
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:54,160
<font size=24>这绝对是我的荣幸</font>
Sir, yes. The honor is mine, absolutely!

268
00:31:55,700 --> 00:32:01,750
<font size=24>这是我们的宫廷作曲家  萨列里大师</font>
Here is our illustrious court composer...Maestro Salieri.

269
00:32:03,250 --> 00:32:06,590
<font size=24>我在你很小时就见过你了</font>
At last, such immense joy!

270
00:32:08,300 --> 00:32:10,340
<font size=24>我很熟悉您的作品</font>
I know your work well.

271
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:15,180
<font size=24>我事实上修改过您的一首作品</font>
You know, I composed some variations on a melody of yours.

272
00:32:15,350 --> 00:32:19,930
<font size=24>-真的?  哪一首?  -《Mio Caro Adone》  -我真是受宠若惊</font>
-Really? Which one? -"Mio Caro Adone." I'm flattered.

273
00:32:20,140 --> 00:32:23,270
<font size=24>那是一首奇怪的小品不过有一些不错的效果</font>
A funny tune, but it yielded good things.

274
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:26,360
<font size=24>他现在回报你的赞美</font>
And now he has returned the compliment.

275
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:30,150
<font size=24>萨列里为你作了一首欢迎你的进行曲</font>
Herr Salieri composed this little march for you.

276
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:32,030
<font size=24>真的?</font>
Really?

277
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:34,150
<font size=24>先生  谢谢你了</font>
Grazie, signore.

278
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:35,860
<font size=24>就是这样子了</font>
Well, there it is.

279
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:41,370
<font size=24>现在我们来谈正事莫扎特  我们要举行一场歌剧</font>
Down to business. We're going to commission an opera from you.

280
00:32:41,620 --> 00:32:43,370
<font size=24>你觉得怎么样?</font>
What do you say?

281
00:32:43,540 --> 00:32:44,620
<font size=24>陛下</font>
Majesty!

282
00:32:44,830 --> 00:32:48,210
<font size=24>我们最后有无作成决定  是采德文或意大利文?</font>
Did we vote in the end for German or Italian?

283
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:54,130
<font size=24>事实上我们最后较倾向  意大利文</font>
Sire, if you remember, we did finally incline to Italian.

284
00:32:54,340 --> 00:32:56,390
<font size=24>有吗?</font>
Did we?

285
00:32:57,510 --> 00:33:01,390
<font size=24>我认为这还没有决定  陛下</font>
I don't think it was really decided, Your Majesty.

286
00:33:02,890 --> 00:33:06,980
<font size=24>-德文...拜托...我们写德文的  -为什么?</font>
-German. Please let it be German. -Why so?

287
00:33:07,190 --> 00:33:11,230
<font size=24>因为我早己找到最精彩的歌词</font>
Because I've already found the most wonderful libretto.

288
00:33:11,650 --> 00:33:13,690
<font size=24>我看过吗?</font>
Have I seen it?

289
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:18,410
<font size=24>院长陛下应该没有!  我的意思是  这剧本是全新的</font>
I don't think you have, Herr Direktor. It's quite new.

290
00:33:18,660 --> 00:33:23,040
<font size=24>我会立刻拿来给你看</font>
-I'll show it to you immediately of course.

291
00:33:23,250 --> 00:33:24,580
<font size=24>介绍一下</font>
Well...

